IP E-Game Venture, Manila Electric: Philippine Stocks Preview

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n
-- 
2011-04-04T01:20:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/ip-e-game-venture-manila-electric-philippine-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index rose 1.8 percent to
4,129.54.  International Container Terminal Services Inc. (ICT)  : An
executive vice president at the largest Philippine port operator
sold 315,900 shares in the open market, a stock exchange filing
showed. The stock was unchanged at 41.70 pesos.  Manila Electric Co. (MER)  : Kilowatt-hour sales at the
nation’s largest electricity retailer may not have grown in the
first quarter amid cooler weather and following last year’s
strong performance, Chief Operating Officer Oscar Reyes told
reporters. The stock rose 2.7 percent to 265 pesos.  Philippine Long Distance Telephone Co. (TEL)  : The
nation’s largest phone company’s unit ePLDT Inc. completed the
sale of a 75 percent stake in an Internet cafe operator to IP E-
Game Ventures Inc. (EG PM). Philippine Long Distance increased
1.4 percent to 2,356 pesos. IP E-Game declined 3.2 percent to 15
pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at 
 dboey@bloomberg.net  